          <h2 class="meta">Phase 2: <span>Monetization</span></h2>
          <p>People use Gather to plan real-world activities, meaning there's an incredibly high purchasing intent. They're going to spend money, they just don't know where. Advertisers can target users they know are picking, say, a funny movie or Mexican restaurant.</p>
          <p>Additionally, most planning with Gather ends with a purchase. Close integration with sites like OpenTable and Fandango means users can make purchases from the app &mdash; and we can take a cut.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="step3">
          <div id="compass"><div id="thingy"></div></div>
          <h2 class="meta">Phase 3: <span>Our Vision</span></h2>
          <p>There's a lot of event planning apps out there. <em> A lot.</em> Most of them are content with just handling RSVPs. Our goal is to mimic how groups make plans, while getting out of the way as much as possible.</p>
